The communication reveals the challenges the government faces politically. To promote BBI, he proposes the President takes charge of rallying leaders to back it. Allies of President Uhuru Kenyatta in Parliament have warned him that the government will lose the Building Bridges Initiative (BBI) referendum in his Mt Kenya backyard and the governor’s race in Nairobi in a bare-knuckle letter seen by the Nation. 

The evaluation is likely to send shock waves in government, coming from the men and women likely to spearhead referendum campaigns for the BBI constitutional Bill. 



