“Whereas I cannot dismiss the candidates who have offered themselves to stand with our party, my hunch feeling (and I could be wrong) tells me competitors on offer have a better trajectory going into the race.” 

Mr Kang’ata explained that some competitors are more eloquent and better at penetrating informal settlements. The Commission has provided accommodation for 60 supervisors at Sh6,500 per day for the 40 days. ODM leader claims IEBC is inflating referendum budget, but Chebukati says he is guided by facts. Pope Francis has accepted his resignation, which came after he attained the mandatory retirement age. Nyeri Town MP Mr Ngunjiri Wambugu said Mr Kang’ata was not sincere in his letter for sharing it with the media and the public. Learning institutions were shut in March to contain the spread of the coronavirus.